( Carnage: Sorry for taking so long to reply with Vlad, Yanshosh. I have 
been busy with Christmas business.)

** Vlad's optics become accustome to the light which fintered in through the 
open hatch-way, blinking a few last times before finally seeing the wall of 
a hallway just beyond the door.
This was a ship...some sort of base.
But what he could tell, it wasn't Maximal, and was more close to the 
Predacon build.
Though, there was no way to find out for sure until he met whom ever this 
ship belonged to, and maybe hire himself an assassin after all.
Vlad smiled and chuckled deeply to himself. Von; if he was alive, would know 
that his little brother came to give him a little visit.

He looks down at the animal at his side for a moment before he begins to 
head for the door, jumping back in surprise as he nearly runs into someone. 
Shesta growling at his side.
It was the man who had dragged him from the sea, recovered the pod, and then 
was taken away.
Growling slighly as he saw the mans hand near his weapon, the growl 
disappearing as he straightened himself up and cleared his throat.
Turning out to look like a rather striking young man, what he wanted to look 
like one.
But Vlad nodded to Havoc's commant.**

" Yes. I don't like living in fish bowls for too long, get's stuffy."

** Vlad didn't smile, only had an expression on his face which reflected the 
brain within. Commented as clever by others. Sneaky and cruel by his 
enemies.
But it was time to get down to business.**

" What faction is this? "
